Class CachedComputerMoreParallelism<A,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sorbonne_u.components.AbstractComponent
      • fr.sorbonne_u.cps.caching.components.CachedComputer<A,V>
        • fr.sorbonne_u.cps.caching.components.CachedComputerMoreParallelism<A,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    fr.sorbonne_u.components.ComponentI, Computable<A,V>

    public class CachedComputerMoreParallelism<A,V>
extends CachedComputer<A,V>
    The class CachedComputerMoreParallelism implements a cached computer that provides a method to compute many values and do so in parallel.

    Description

    The component defined by CachedComputer<A,V> already allows many values to be computed in parallel when multiple clients call the method compute in parallel. Here, a method computeAll takes many arguments and compute their results in parallel, showing how to "generate" parallelism using executor service tools within a BCM component.

    Invariant

     invariant              true

    Created on : 2020-03-11

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant
